    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Given : Yield stress, $f_y=250 \\mathrm{MPa}$ </p>\n<p>Dimension, $a=100 \\mathrm{~mm}$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m0t2cxm9/b8a435b0-9d88-4c3a-99b5-52e090622bd7/5c5e6a10-6d99-11ef-917d-3fcf65870137/file-jaoe38c1m0t2cxma.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m0t2cxm9/b8a435b0-9d88-4c3a-99b5-52e090622bd7/5c5e6a10-6d99-11ef-917d-3fcf65870137/file-jaoe38c1m0t2cxma.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2022 Set 2 Structural Analysis - Plastic Analysis Question 2 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; a=100 \\mathrm{~m} \\\\ &amp; b=100 \\sqrt{2} \\mathrm{~mm} \\\\ &amp; h=\\frac{100 \\sqrt{2}}{2}=\\frac{100}{\\sqrt{2}} \\mathrm{~mm} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>We know that,</p>\n<p>Shape factor for diamond section $=2$</p>\n<p>Now plastic moment $=$ Section plastic modulus $\\times$ Yield stress</p>\n<p>$\\begin{aligned} M_P &amp; =Z_P \\times f_y \\\\\\\\ M_P &amp; =\\frac{A}{2} \\times\\left(y_1+y_2\\right) \\times f_y \\\\\\\\ &amp; =\\frac{2 \\times \\frac{b h}{2}}{2}\\left(y_1+y_2\\right) \\times f_y\\end{aligned}$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m0t2fbhg/7f12d21e-ad26-4b9d-9225-a3ee57fb298a/9eb2da40-6d99-11ef-917d-3fcf65870137/file-jaoe38c1m0t2fbhh.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m0t2fbhg/7f12d21e-ad26-4b9d-9225-a3ee57fb298a/9eb2da40-6d99-11ef-917d-3fcf65870137/file-jaoe38c1m0t2fbhh.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2022 Set 2 Structural Analysis - Plastic Analysis Question 2 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>$M_P=\\frac{100 \\sqrt{2} \\times \\frac{100}{\\sqrt{2}}}{2} \\times\\left(\\frac{h}{3} \\times 2\\right) \\times 250$</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; M_P=5000 \\times\\left(\\frac{100}{\\sqrt{2} \\times 3} \\times 2\\right) \\times 250 \\\\ &amp; M_P=58.92 \\mathrm{kN}-\\mathrm{m} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Hence, the correct option is (C).</p>",
