    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Consider the beam section shown in the figure, with $y$ indicating the depth of neutral axis (NA). The section is only subjected to an increasing bending moment. It is given that $y=18.75 \\mathrm{~mm}$, when the section has not yielded at the top and bottom fibres. Further, $y$ decreases to 5 mm , when the entire section has yielded. The shape factor of the section is ________ (rounded off to 2 decimal places).</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbj0r373/f397aca8-e7eb-463b-ac9c-4d35e1fea4f1/9e6bf7f0-41d9-11f0-a8bb-41428e2c0e84/file-jaoe38c1mbj0r374.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbj0r373/f397aca8-e7eb-463b-ac9c-4d35e1fea4f1/9e6bf7f0-41d9-11f0-a8bb-41428e2c0e84/file-jaoe38c1mbj0r374.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2025 Set 1 Structural Analysis - Plastic Analysis Question 1 English\">",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "answer": "1.80TO1.82",
    "explanation": "<p>$$ \\text { For plastic section modulus }\\left(Z_p\\right)=\\frac{A}{2}\\left(y_c+y_t\\right) $$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbj0saig/5ac027f2-6e50-4e9c-9ab8-70128c5c710e/bfe1cb80-41d9-11f0-a8bb-41428e2c0e84/file-jaoe38c1mbj0saih.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbj0saig/5ac027f2-6e50-4e9c-9ab8-70128c5c710e/bfe1cb80-41d9-11f0-a8bb-41428e2c0e84/file-jaoe38c1mbj0saih.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2025 Set 1 Structural Analysis - Plastic Analysis Question 1 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp;\\begin{aligned} Z_p &amp; =\\frac{A}{2}\\left(y_c+y_t\\right) \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{2 \\times 60 \\times 5}{2}(2.5+30) \\\\ Z_p &amp; =9750 \\mathrm{~mm}^3 \\end{aligned}\\\\ &amp;\\text { For elastic section modulus }\\left(Z_e\\right)=\\frac{I_{N A}}{y_{\\max }} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbj0tbal/2a65effb-7421-412b-b8d2-c4e192672866/dc4b81d0-41d9-11f0-a8bb-41428e2c0e84/file-jaoe38c1mbj0tbam.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbj0tbal/2a65effb-7421-412b-b8d2-c4e192672866/dc4b81d0-41d9-11f0-a8bb-41428e2c0e84/file-jaoe38c1mbj0tbam.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE CE 2025 Set 1 Structural Analysis - Plastic Analysis Question 1 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>Area moment of inertia about NA</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} I_{N A} &amp; =\\left[\\frac{60 \\times 5^3}{12}+60 \\times 5(16.25)^2\\right]+\\left[\\frac{5 \\times 60^3}{12}+5 \\times 60 \\times(16.25)^2\\right] \\\\ I_{N A} &amp; =249062.5 \\mathrm{~mm}^4 \\\\ y_{\\max } &amp; =46.25 \\mathrm{~mm} \\\\ Z_e &amp; =\\frac{I_{N A}}{y_{\\max }}=\\frac{249062.5 \\mathrm{~mm}^4}{46.25 \\mathrm{~mm}} \\\\ Z_e &amp; =5385.135 \\mathrm{~mm}^3 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p></p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned}Now, \\,\\,\\,shape\\,\\,\\, factor\\,\\,\\, S &amp; =\\frac{M_P}{M_y}=\\frac{f_y Z_p}{f_y Z_e} \\\\ &amp; =\\frac{9750 \\mathrm{~mm}^3}{5385.135 \\mathrm{~mm}^3} \\\\ S &amp; =1.81 \\end{aligned} $$</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "gate-ce-2025-set-1",
    "difficulty": null
  },
